article_title: Trading Volumes at Discount Brokers Pull Back From Record Levels
article_text:
Small investors are taking their feet off the gas pedal.

One year after discount brokerage firms reported record trading activity, the latest batch of trading-volume data shows a more tempered enthusiasm among individual traders at some of the largest online brokerages.

Average daily client trades that generated revenue at E*Trade Financial Corp. and TD Ameritrade Holding Corp. during the last quarter pulled back from record...
